# examples/hello_world.clyp
# A simple "Hello, World!" program in Clyp.
# It demonstrates variable declaration, function definition, and printing to the console.

str name = "World";
print("Hello, " + name + "!");

# Define a function to greet someone.
# It takes a string argument and returns a new string.
function greet(str person) returns str {
    return "Greetings, " + person + "!";
};

# Call the function and print the result.
print(greet("Clyp Developer"));
